description: 15 prints : many color ; 44 x 58 cm. or smaller. | European prints of celebrations, ceremonies, and other events featuring balloons or early balloon flight. Subjects are varied and include festivities in honor of the French Republic and Bastille Day; fairs and festivals; political pageants; a British fund raising event; the opening of New London bridge; the coronation of George IV, King of Great Britain, in 1821; and the Siege of Paris.

related_items.title: Berlin, Germany, 1918
description: 22 photomechanical prints ; 18 x 24 cm. | 4 photographic prints ; 11 x 16 cm. or smaller. | Reproductions of paintings and photographs of revolutionary actions in 1918 in Berlin, Germany and Vienna, Austria. Includes gatherings of people in the streets; troops trying to quell a general strike; funeral cortege of the revolutionary casualties passing through the streets; demonstrations; group portraits of leaders of political factions, such as the Deutsche Volkspartei (German People's Party), the Christian People's Party, the Central Council of the Socialist Republic of Berlin. Also photographs of the German 7th Field Artillery Regiment on parade; ceremony with German Reichspresident Ebert and R.W.M. Noske turning over the Bavarian army to the German army, and a gathering of demonstrators on "Avignon-Sonntag" in Berlin.
